{{Lowercase title}}
The '''iBooks Author Conference''' is an annual gathering of the user community of Apple's [[iBooks Author]] digital content creation software, including educators,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://classtechtips.com/2015/08/09/ibooks-author-conference-october-8th-9th-nashville-tn/|title=iBooks Author Conference: October 8th & 9th – Nashville, TN|work=Class Tech Tips|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref> creative professionals, marketing professionals, entrepreneurs, corporate trainers, self-published authors, and many others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diyauthor.com/media-from-the-2015-ibooks-author-conference/|title=Media from the 2015 iBooks Author Conference|author=Chris Well|work=DIY Author|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/17-ways-use-ibooks-author-right-now-bradley-metrock|title=17 Ways To Use iBooks Author Right Now|date=August 3, 2015|language=en|access-date=January 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://storify.com/hooperc97/ibooks-author-conference-2015|title=iBooks Author Conference 2015|work=Storify|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref>  "The iBAs," the awards recognizing achievement in iBooks Author production, are part of the iBooks Author Conference and recognize books and individuals from around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hon.jp/news/modules/rsnavi/showarticle.php?id=6865|title=米国で第1回「The iBooks Author Conference」開催、日本のアニメ原画集「セロ弾きのゴーシュ 資料集」が受賞|author=info@hon.jp|work=hon.jp|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peterpappas.com/tag/ibooks-author|title=iBooks Author " Tag Archive " Copy / Paste by Peter Pappas|publisher=peterpappas.com|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.savvybookwriters.com/tag/ibooks-author-certification/|title=IBooks Author Certification – Savvy Book Writers|publisher=savvybookwriters.com|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref>

==2015 iBooks Author Conference==
The 2015 iBooks Author Conference took place at the [[Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum]] in [[Nashville, Tennessee]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.macnews.com/2015/08/06/ibooks-author-conference-coming-nashville-tn-october|title=iBooks Author Conference coming to Nashville, TN, in October {{!}} MacTech|website=www.macnews.com|language=en|access-date=January 23, 2017}}</ref> with [[Apple Inc.|Apple]], [[NASA]], Southwest, HCA, and other large companies in attendance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://southernalpha.com/apple-nasa-southwest-headed-to-nashville-for-ibooks-author-conference/|title=Apple, NASA, Southwest headed to Nashville for iBooks Author Conference|author=Ayumi Fukuda Bennett|work=SouthernAlpha|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref> Keynote speakers for the inaugural iBooks Author Conference<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibooksauthorconference.com|title=The iBooks Author Conference October 8–9 – Nashville, Tennessee|work=The iBooks Author Conference – October 8–9 – Nashville, Tennessee|accessdate=October 20, 2015}}</ref> included Kelly Gabrysch, Director of Digital Publishing at Trailer Park Los Angeles, Dr. Julia Maurer of [[Mercersburg Academy]] (PA), and the co-creators of The Mozart Project, an interactive book created used iBooks Author.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.talkingnewmedia.com/2015/05/29/team-behind-the-mozart-project-to-headline-the-ibooks-author-conference-in-october/|title=Team behind The Mozart Project to headline the iBooks Author Conference in October|publisher=talkingnewmedia.com|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JGCCzh8lHYg|title=The Mozart Project co-creators headline the iBooks Author Conference|date=August 16, 2015|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=October 20, 2015}}</ref>

==2016 iBooks Author Conference==
The 2016 iBooks Author Conference took place at the [[Gaylord Opryland Resort & Convention Center]] on October 6–7, 2016.  The keynote was provided by [[Southwest Airlines]], which uses iBooks Author to create their company-wide training curriculum (called "Southwest Airlines University").  Apple was the largest attendees of the conference, with an entire international business unit attending.

==2017 iBooks Author Conference==
The 2017 iBooks Author Conference<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-2017-ibooks-author-conference-tickets-28565450030}}</ref> has been announced for October 12–13, 2017, on the campus of [[Vanderbilt University]].  The keynote will be provided by NASA, which has used iBooks Author extensively and most recently to create the multi-touch book ''Destination: Jupiter'', which tells the story of the successful [[Juno mission]].  Southwest Airlines, the newest major sponsor of the event, will provide a reception for attendees during the event.

